# Hokuyo drivers

This software is constructed according to the Pods software policies and
templates. The policies and templates can be found at:

  http://sourceforge.net/projects/pods


## Use it in Docker

To use the hokuyo drivers in a Docker container, clone the repository and run the following command to
build the image:

```
docker build [ARGUMENTS] -t ripl-ttic/hokuyo ./
```

You can specify build arguments using the syntax `--build-arg KEY1=VALUE1 KEY2=VALUE2 ...`

#### Available ARGUMENTS

- `INSTALL_DIR`:  Path, inside the container, where to install the drivers. Default is `/root/hokuyo/build`.
